title: Build failure of video detection should allow cancelling of video run in one click
body: Currently shows individual video detection task for re-run. When a video is run against many models (say > 20) and the run fails, there will be 20 different video detection tasks to rerun. In such cases, there might be a race condition in which the backend will pick up some video detection tasks to run in one instance and some other detection tasks for the same video to run in another instance.

title: Admin interface to enable "released model"
body:
Ability for an admin to select different versions of built models to be marked as "released" for video evaluation purposes. Propose two kinds of releases:

1. "RELEASE_TEST" 
  - For temporarily enabling video testing on model.
  - All models marked with this release label will be automatically added when a new video is entered for evaluation.
  - Multiple model versions can have this release label.
2. "RELEASE_FINAL" 
  - For enabling video evaluation in `cellroti`.
  - All models marked as "RELEASE_FINAL" is automatically also treated as "RELEASE_TEST".
  - All models marked with this release label will be automatically added when a new video is entered for evaluation
  - One and only one model version MUST have this release label.

title: Large thumbnails not showing on double click of small thumbnails
body:
Regression due to Issue 18.

When expiring URL was implemented, the time for expiration was made 30 seconds. The large thumbnail URL get generated during initial page load. 30 seconds is insufficient time to browse through all images in a page.

Solution 1:
* Get large thumbnail URL on-demand when the user double clicks on a thumbnail
* Requires AJAX call to get new URL. Difficult

Solution 2:
* Increase time out to 30 minutes
* No change in AJAX and easier to implement. It is less secure but 30 minutes should be a small enough window to browse a significant number of images to steal.

Documentation will be a long slow process that will be driven by bug fixing and available free time. Put tools in place to enable this process.

title: Upload of video fails in HTTPS
body: Regression issue caused by fix of issue 17. Large file upload is failing perhaps due to encryption on client side.

title: Support "ImageBank" functionality
body:
Capability:
* Ability to quickly rank detection score on ~15K images for each model iteration.
* Ability to copy/paste selective images from image bank to next model iteration

Not supported:
* Adding images to bank through UI
* Tagging images
* Deleting images

title: Enabl local develepment without S3
body:
Create a new environment to support local development in addition to production and development which use S3 and need talk to python backend. The local environment will talk to local MySQL database and store files locally.

Will help in rapid code iteration without waiting for EC2 uploads/synchs to happen.

title: Add orphaned images page + Admin interface
body: So images in S3 with no link to any model can be reassigned to another model or deleted by user with appropriate permission. Currently, no way to see these orphaned images once removed from last model's list.

title: Use more robust server setup than WEBbrick
body: Transition to either NGINX or Apache as server (keep Mongrel as application layer?)

title: Manage production and development environment
body:
1. Need two sets of buckets for production and development work.
2. Port 80 always gets production environment and port 3000 gets development environment.

title: Change database to MySQL
body:
SQLite may not scale to large number of read/writes. 

* Switch to MySQL for rails backend.
* Support backups

title: Limit access to image URLs in S3
body: Anyone can access images using S3 URLs - even when not logged in.

title: Support https
Timeout user session after 24 hours
body: Change devise settings to support this

title: Regression caused by issue 7 - need to rollback changes
body:
Individual file progress bar is messed up:
 1. All progress bar have the same % complete ratio
 2. The main progress bar doesn't show actual progress

title: Default image view in small thumbnail?
body: Faster page update and reduces page scroll.

title: Show score with all test images after model is built
body:
Once model is built, all test images show associated scores.
Show TP, FN, FP, TN alongside the scores under each image, color coded is even better. (word "Score" can be removed for space, esp. in small thumbnail view)

Currently, only way to view test score is via "view" button next to TP, FN, FP, TN.

title: FP/TP scores - 0.0%
body:
Either:

1. It is not multiplied to 100%. Needs to show 2 decimal points
OR
2. It is not sorted in the right order

title: Matlab charts half of original size
body:
Largest chart was supposed to be 800px wide. It is only 300px wide.

This causes truncation of smaller charts.

title: Test image count not adding up
body:
In the show model page, after model is built, following not happening:

Num of (TP + FN = Positive test)
Num of (FP + TN = Negative test)

title: Checkout button from index page clickable when in build queue
body:
Reproduction:

1. Check out model and follow steps to take model to final build state
2. Click on Build button -> Model goes in build queue state and progress bar is shown
3. Before starting python script, go to index page
4. Model is still "checkoutable"

title: Clipboard empty when visiting from one model to another
body:
Reproduction:

1. Create ModelA,V1 by User1
2. Create ModelB,V1 by User2
3. Copy images from ModelA to clipboard
4. Navigate to ModelB --> Clipboard is empty

title: Show remaining number of images to be uploaded during upload
body:
For large number of images, it is not clear when all uploads are done. Scrolling down the page to check the progress bar seems to be the only way now and can be missed. Something like a display near top of page showing "remaining number of images to upload" with the count will be helpful. 

Current display of "Number of  images in .." is useful when we're building the set with multiple uploads.

title: Show user who Checkedout a model
body: In "Open existing model" page, it'll be helpful to show who has a model checked out alongside "Checkedout" button.

title: Image not selected nor enlarged on click/double-click in small thumbnail view
body:
Under view image mode, image is not selected in small thumbnail mode (with red box) similar to that in large thumbnail mode. "All" or "None" using selection button, however, works in both modes. Selection with red box in large thumbnail mode is also carried over in small thumbnail mode correctly, but can't be changed in caes of individual image.

Similarly, image enlargement on double-click is not working in small thumbnail viewing mode.

(firefox 24.0, vista)

title: Check for minimum number of images before model building starts
body: For both train and test sets. Currently, match to zero image is allowing model building without any image upload. Setting a minimum number of images, say 50 for training and 10 for testing may be good.

title: Different background color hues for clipboard page
body: (Starting to use github for this) Use page background color hues to indicate different functional context, such as making clipboard page background light blue (say). So it is easily clear to the user where s/he is during image selection/add/delete. Background color needs to be mellow to eyes and low contrast. Similarly, video/train/test page could have different color hues. (To be kept for later if too time consuming)

title: Create web page title for each page
Building a new model crashes
body:
Bug: Crash occurs because 'show' action is not defined due to navigasmic gem. 

Fix: Using a different 'showModel' action and updated routes file.

Todo: Delete original 'show' action and update all references. Better yet, figure out why navigasmic causes 'show' to crash.
